cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as aspect term extraction. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses unsupervised learning techniques to develop a novel approach. Additionally, it may fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of neural networks for modeling dependency paths. It could also be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as aspect term extraction is a sub-task of information retrieval. Finally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses recurrent neural networks for modeling dependency paths.
